# Project Standards

Credit management system built with Next.js 14, TypeScript, Drizzle ORM (Turso/SQLite), NextAuth v5, and shadcn/ui.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Database**: Turso (SQLite) with Drizzle ORM
- **Auth**: NextAuth v5 (beta)
- **UI**: shadcn/ui + Radix UI + Tailwind CSS
- **Package Manager**: pnpm

## Naming Conventions
- Files/folders: `kebab-case`
- Components: `PascalCase`
- Variables/functions: `camelCase`
- Use TypeScript with strict type checking

## Language & Localization
- **All user-facing text MUST be in Spanish**
- Format currency as Colombian Pesos (COP) using `formatCOP()`
- Use date-fns for date manipulation
- Consistent Spanish terminology for financial concepts

## File Organization
```
src/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router pages
├── components/       # Reusable UI components
│   ├── ui/          # shadcn/ui base components
│   ├── modals/      # Modal components
│   └── dashboard/   # Dashboard components
├── lib/             # Utilities and configurations
│   └── actions/     # Server actions
├── db/              # Database schema
├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
└── types/           # TypeScript definitions
```

## Error Handling
- Wrap DB operations in try-catch blocks
- Log errors to console for debugging
- Provide meaningful Spanish error messages
- Use toast notifications for user feedback

## Security
- Validate all inputs on client AND server
- Use server actions for sensitive operations
- Hash passwords with bcryptjs (10 rounds)
- Store secrets in environment variables
